{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS-1 review [G6 — approach soundness / anti-patterns / alternative-selection]: PASS, no findings.\n\nGrounded in src/rebar/llm/runner.py:209-303,421-435 and src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py:173-182,256-270.\n\nAffirmations:\n- MECHANISM CORRECTNESS: caching the SYSTEM PROMPT is the correct lever — the re-sent stable bytes (whole parent plan) are rendered into system_prompt via _resolve_system (passes.py:257), not the user message. anthropic_cache_instructions places cache_control on the system-prompt block for rebar's no-instruction-parts shape (runner.py:212-214). Retry path holds: _pai_structured rebuilds only the user `prompt`, passing `kwargs` (system_prompt + model_settings) unchanged (runner.py:368/372-391) — so caching survives the bounded retry exactly as the plan claims (\"structured-output retry path untouched\").\n- FITNESS-FOR-PURPOSE: caches the actual re-sent bytes, not a proxy; AC#3 (cache_read_input_tokens > 0 on a repeat container call) is a real end-to-end proof the mechanism works, not a surrogate.\n- APPROACH SELECTION: generated alternatives — (a) user-message CachePoint on the parent plan, (b) routing the stable plan through instructions= to cache there. (a) is defensibly worse (changes the content-list, perturbs the structured-retry path, and the stable bytes aren't even in the user message); (b) is the plan's own spike-contingent fallback. Chosen seam approach is at-least-as-good on blast-radius (no content-list change), codebase-alignment (single shared runner seam), and testability. No clearly-superior missed alternative — discarded.\n- POSITIVE RATIONALE present and strong: \"the re-sent stable bytes ... live in the SYSTEM PROMPT ... so the correct, minimal lever is caching the SYSTEM PROMPT\" plus the anthropic-gating rationale (keys error on openai/gemini).\n- SPIKE-contingency is sound, not a defect: the mechanism is gated on a verifiable spike with a pre-committed documented fallback, so the approach is robust to either spike outcome."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782577472727363001,"uuid":"30c5009f-1af1-4a51-a0b9-b56739332307"}